          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Rosianna by: </span>
      Mr Lapish
  </div>


    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer11385384" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15391872492658156026">Absolutely fantastic, and entirely unputdownable. At first you&apos;re unsure what kind of route Harris is going to take on Vesuvius&apos; eruption as it opens with talk of aqueducts and engineers, but in the space of a few hundred pages, he recreates the bay of Naples vividly and realistically, so you really do feel get an idea of the timescale and the emotions, all built in to this great read.</span>
  <span id="freeText15391872492658156026" style="display:none">Absolutely fantastic, and entirely unputdownable. At first you're unsure what kind of route Harris is going to take on Vesuvius' eruption as it opens with talk of aqueducts and engineers, but in the space of a few hundred pages, he recreates the bay of Naples vividly and realistically, so you really do feel get an idea of the timescale and the emotions, all built in to this great read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15391872492658156026" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

